# Prerequisites & Pre-Flight Checks

## API Key / Credential Validation

Before starting any workflow that uses an MCP server, verify the required credentials exist.
Do not proceed if credentials are missing — inform the user immediately.

| MCP Server | Required Credentials | Config Location |
|------------|---------------------|----------------|
| BlazeMeter | `BLAZEMETER_API_KEY`, `BLAZEMETER_API_SECRET` | `.env` or environment variables |
| Datadog | `DD_API_KEY`, `DD_APP_KEY` | `.env` or environment variables |
| Confluence | `CONFLUENCE_TOKEN`, `CONFLUENCE_USER` (cloud) or `CONFLUENCE_PAT` (onprem) | `.env` or environment variables |
| Azure DevOps | ADO MCP configured, or manual access to ADO | ADO MCP config or manual |

## Artifact Structure

- `test_run_id` is always required for any workflow
- If the user does not provide one, ask. As a fallback, generate as `YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM-SS`
- Artifacts directory: `artifacts/{test_run_id}/`
- Canonical subfolder structure:

```
artifacts/{test_run_id}/
├── blazemeter/       # BlazeMeter CSV, logs, session data
├── datadog/          # Host/k8s metrics, logs, APM traces
├── analysis/         # PerfAnalysis JSON outputs
├── reports/          # Generated reports, revisions, metadata
├── charts/           # Generated PNG chart images
└── jmeter/           # JMX scripts, network captures, correlation files
```

- Test comparison artifacts use: `artifacts/comparisons/{comparison_id}/`
- File existence checks are mandatory gates between workflows

## Environment Configuration

- Verify the environment name exists in Datadog MCP configuration before starting a Datadog workflow
- Missing environments cause mid-workflow failures — validate upfront

## MCP Server Availability

- If an MCP server is not available, inform the user which MCP server is unavailable and ask for next steps (e.g. skip the unavailable MCP workflow? Stop and wait for the MCP to become available?)
- Do not fail silently

## Configuration Files Reference

| MCP Server   | Config File                                               | Purpose                                        |
|--------------|-----------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| JMeter       | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | JMeter paths, browser settings, think time     |
| JMeter       | `jmeter_config.yaml`                                      | JMX generation settings, verbose logging       |
| JMeter       | `correlation_config.yaml`                                 | Custom naming mappings for correlations        |
| BlazeMeter   | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | BlazeMeter API settings, max artifact download retries, shared folder allowed extensions |
| Datadog      | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | Datadog API pagination limits                  |
| Datadog      | `environments.json`                                       | Host/k8s/services definitions per environment  |
| Datadog      | `custom_queries.json`                                     | Custom log, APM, and timeseries metric queries |
| PerfAnalysis | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | Analysis settings, resouce thresholds, bottleneck analysis settings |
| PerfAnalysis | `slas.yaml`                                               | SLA configurations for response times and error rate thresholds     |
| PerfReport   | `report_config.yaml`                                      | Report sections, revisable sections, unit display                   |
| PerfReport   | `chart_schema.yaml`                                       | Chart definitions, unit configuration                               |
| PerfReport   | `chart_colors.yaml`                                       | Color palettes for charts                                           |
| Confluence   | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | Pagination limits                              |
| Streamlit    | `config.yaml` / `config.mac.yaml` / `config.windows.yaml` | Port settings, page title                      |
